jobs.prompt:
Build the five panel pages plus the backing snapshot endpoint.

Backend: Code&DBs/Workflow/surfaces/api/handlers/mobile_metrics.py — GET /mobile/metrics/snapshot returns compact JSON:
- flow { in_flight, queued, planned, finished_24h, failed_24h, jobs_per_worker }
- economy { spend_today_cents, spend_week_cents, budget_remaining_cents, burn_rate_cents_per_hour, http_429_count_1h }
- providers { anthropic, openai, gemini, deepseek } each with { health, circuit_state, active_fallback }
- quality { bugs_open, bugs_critical, self_heal_events_24h, friction_events_24h, pending_approvals }
- system { worker_alive, heartbeat_lag_s, migrations_pending }

Frontend: pages under surfaces/app/src/mobile/pages/panels/:
- FlowPanel.tsx, EconomyPanel.tsx, ProvidersPanel.tsx, QualityPanel.tsx, SystemPanel.tsx. Compact grid of 4-6 key-value rows; no charts, sparklines, or tables. Numeric-only.
- All panels poll /mobile/metrics/snapshot every 10s when visible.

Constraints:
- No panel introduces a metric beyond those listed. Missing metric? Add to the snapshot endpoint, not a second endpoint.
- Zero scrolling at 844px viewport (standard modern-phone baseline; covers Pixel, Galaxy, and iPhone mid-range). If it would scroll, drop rows until it fits.

Integration test at tests/integration/test_mobile_metrics.py + frontend test at surfaces/app/src/mobile/__tests__/panels.test.tsx.
